message.content:
The term "European Union" has two different meanings: 

1. On one hand, it refers to the 27 European countries that have joined together in an economic and political partnership aimed at promoting peace, stability, and prosperity throughout the continent. These countries are Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Croatia, Cyprus, Czech Republic, Denmark, Estonia,Romania , Finland . France , Germany , Greece , Hungary , Ireland Italy Latvia Lithuania Luxembourg Malta Netherlands Poland Portugal Slovakia Slovenia Spain Sweden.

2. On another hand,it's also a reference to the institutions responsible for creating and implementing policies on behalf of its member states. The main EU institutions include:

- European Commission: This body proposes new laws while also administering them
- Council of European Union : It represents governments of each Member State
- European Parliament : Represents interests of citizens by elected members
